  "title": "Operations Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role Overview</strong></p><p>The  Operations Manager will be responsible for the day-to-day operational performance of outlets. This role ensures that our stores deliver excellent customer experience, operational efficiency, and strong financial results. Reporting to the COO, the Operations Manager will work closely with store managers, kitchen teams, and the back office to execute processes, maintain standards, and support growth.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>• Oversee daily operations across outlets to ensure smooth, efficient, and consistent execution.</p><p>• Support teams in staffing, training, scheduling, and performance management.</p><p>• Monitor operational KPIs including sales, labor costs, and food costs; recommend improvements where needed.</p><p>• Implement and maintain standard operating procedures (SOPs) to ensure quality, food safety, and customer\nservice standards.</p><p>• Drive outlet-level initiatives to improve efficiency, reduce waste, and enhance customer experience.</p><p>• Coordinate with the marketing team to support local activations and promotions.</p><p>• Ensure compliance with regulatory requirements, health & safety standards, and company policies.</p><p>• Provide feedback and insights from the ground to senior management to inform decision-making.</p><p><strong>Qualifications & Experience</strong></p><p>• Minimum 1-2 years of proven operations management experience.</p><p>• Strong leadership skills with the ability to motivate and support teams in a fast-paced, high-volume environment.</p><p>• Hands-on operator who thrives in solving problems and improving processes.</p><p>• Proficient with operational and financial metrics; comfortable with POS and scheduling systems.</p><p>• Excellent communication and organizational skills.</p>",
